<h2 class='portfolio-heading'>The Last Heart (Winter 2022)</h2>
    <div class="portfolio-item">

        <div class='portfolio-desc'>

        <p class='portfolio-text'>
            <i>In Nequam Mountain the undead seeks to rise again. Warriors from the past have left items to aid you quest,
            but every boon has its cost. Will you be able to defeat the enemy within and save your people?</i>
            <br><br>
            For this project, the team wanted to create an extremely unforgiving hack-and-slash RPG.
            She was responsible for coordinating all group members by creating a development plan,
            running meetings, and keeping track of tasks to complete.
            She also contributed to level design, programming, story, and other assorted art.
            <br><br>
            Other Credits:
            <br>
            Engine: Construct3, free version
            <br><br>
            Made for CMPM 80k at UCSC taught by Tad Leckman and Noah Wardrip-Fruin
        </p>

        </div>

        

